Report on Prison Admission Trends in the U.S.

Simon Cao

2/25/2022

Introduction

The data set used in this analysis is from this repository. The dataset provides county-level data on incarceration in the U.S. with 153,811 observations and 121 variables.

The United States has a significant problem in racial justice, especially in racial discrimination by law enforcement. In this analysis, we focus on the U.S. prison admission rate of people of color to identify the unfairness.

Summary Information

  • The prison admission rate below is established on a per 100,000 people basis. It is clear that through 2011 to 2016, people of color suffer significant larger prison admission rate than average with the black population stands out ( greater than 1000 admission rate).
